 Farmers that do adopt in the control group do so because the they believe
 the misspecified adoption premium exceeds the cost of the seed.
 Informing them about the true nature of the production function will reduce
 the likelihood of adoption, as the information increases the cost side
 of the equation.
 Only if the misspecified adoption premium is assumed to be large enough
 (that is exceeding the cost of the additional complementary inputs needed
